  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators hypothesize that leg edema will decrease rapidly when using the NormaTec
      pump, patients will lose weight, will feel better, will be less prone to infections in their
      legs and to congestion of the liver. Temporary elevation of intravascular fluid volume by the
      mobilized edema fluid returned to the intravascular space by pumping may increase cardiac
      output and renal perfusion and in addition it may distend the right atrium and ventricle thus
      inducing BNP secretion. Both mechanisms may promote excess fluid removal by the kidneys.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
