  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  hemodynamically stable adult patients with pronounced leg edema from any etiology, on
             optimal medical therapy (such as diuretics, ACE-I or ARBs, digoxin).

          -  documentation of right heart failure by Echo or other modality (CT, MRI, right heart
             catheterization) and hemodynamic data from Echo is required and an elevated pulmonary
             artery pressure (&gt; 35 mmHg) is expected in such cases.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  patients in sepsis,

          -  hemodynamically unstable,

          -  during an acute attack of pulmonary edema,

          -  with renal failure (creatinine &gt; 2 mg%),

          -  with DVT,

          -  psychiatric or noncompliant patients, and

          -  patients who will not sign the informed consent form will be excluded from the study.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
